  "text": "Node.js implements comprehensive prototype pollution prevention throughout its core utilities using multiple defense mechanisms:\n\n## Primary Defense Mechanisms\n\n### 1. Primordials Module (lib/internal/per_context/primordials.js)\nThe primordials module is the cornerstone of Node.js's defense against prototype pollution. It stores immutable references to built-in JavaScript objects before user code can modify them. Key patterns include:\n- Safe iterators created with ObjectSetPrototypeOf(SafeIterator.prototype, null) to prevent prototype chain traversal\n- SafeMap, SafeSet, SafeWeakMap, SafeWeakSet classes created using makeSafe() function that freezes prototypes\n- ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty imported from primordials for safe property checks\n- All primordials object itself frozen with ObjectSetPrototypeOf(primordials, null) and ObjectFreeze(primordials)\n\n### 2. Intrinsic Freezing (lib/internal/freeze_intrinsics.js)\nThis file implements deep freezing of all JavaScript intrinsic objects (built-in prototypes and constructors). The deepFreeze() function:\n- Uses SafeSet for tracking frozen objects\n- Employs ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty checks to verify property ownership\n- Freezes all fundamental objects, collection prototypes, typed arrays, and error constructors\n- Prevents runtime modification of Object.prototype, Array.prototype, and other critical prototypes\n\n## Safe Object Patterns\n\n### 3. Object Creation with __proto__: null\nMultiple files use Object.create(null) or descriptor objects with __proto__: null to create objects without prototype chain access:\n- lib/internal/error_serdes.js: Creates empty objects for collecting properties\n- lib/internal/options.js: Schema objects use __proto__: null\n- lib/quic.js: Module exports use ObjectCreate(null)\n- lib/stream.js: Property descriptors use __proto__: null\n- lib/internal/perf/nodetiming.js: Descriptor definitions use __proto__: null\n\n### 4. Safe Collection Usage\nFiles extensively use SafeMap and SafeSet instead of regular Map/Set to prevent prototype pollution through collection manipulation:\n- lib/internal/watch_mode/files_watcher.js: Uses SafeMap for watchers and SafeSet for filtered files\n- lib/internal/fs/glob.js: SafeMap for caching, SafeSet for cache sets\n- lib/internal/console/constructor.js: SafeMap for inspect options, SafeWeakMap for console options\n- lib/internal/bootstrap/realm.js: SafeMap for builtin module caching\n- lib/internal/modules/esm/translators.js: SafeMap for translation caches\n\n## Property Ownership Checks\n\n### 5. ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty Pattern\nFiles use ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty from primordials for safe property existence checks:\n- lib/buffer.js: Checks constructor.name property ownership\n- lib/child_process.js: Verifies option environment properties\n- lib/internal/validators.js: Validates internal field existence\n- lib/internal/crypto/util.js: Checks algorithm property ownership\n- lib/internal/util/inspect.js: Inspects options and property ownership\n- lib/internal/freeze_intrinsics.js: Checks descriptor property ownership in deep freeze\n- lib/internal/modules/helpers.js: Verifies conditions property ownership\n\n## Derived Patterns\n\n### 6. WebIDL and Type Converters\nlib/internal/webidl.js and lib/internal/crypto/webidl.js implement safe type conversion:\n- Dictionary converters that avoid polluting prototypes\n- Safe reflection using ReflectGetOwnPropertyDescriptor\n- Validation without relying on user-modifiable Object methods\n\n### 7. Protected Prototype Chaining\nlib/internal/streams/duplex.js and similar files use ObjectSetPrototypeOf with descriptor objects having __proto__: null to prevent prototype-based attacks during stream setup.\n\n## Execution Context Protection\n\n### 8. Module-Level Freezing\nlib/internal/per_context/primordials.js freezes its export object entirely:\n- ObjectSetPrototypeOf(primordials, null) removes prototype chain\n- ObjectFreeze(primordials) prevents property modification\n- Creates immutable reference to safe built-ins for all modules\n\n### 9. Service Layer Protection\nKey services like lib/internal/error_serdes.js use safe object creation patterns:\n- TryGetAllProperties uses ObjectCreate(null) with __proto__: null\n- ObjectAssign with safe patterns avoids prototype traversal\n- HasOwnProperty checks throughout error serialization\n\n## Summary\nNode.js's prototype pollution prevention is multi-layered:\n1. **Primordials** provide safe references to built-in objects\n2. **Safe Collections** (SafeMap, SafeSet) prevent collection-based attacks\n3. **Object.create(null)** creates objects without prototype chains\n4. **ObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty** performs safe property checks\n5. **Deep Freezing** prevents runtime modification of intrinsics\n6. **Descriptor Pattern** with __proto__: null prevents descriptor pollution\n\nThese patterns are applied consistently across 50+ core files to defend against both direct and indirect prototype pollution attacks."
}

